but maybe they're not present here.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031493,0.067409,0.079857,0.086605,0.091543,0.095229,0.10022,0.1014,0.099068,0.094518,0.087037,0.065626],"unified_progress":[0.037575,0.065381,0.076723,0.085163,0.09403,0.094559,0.098427,0.10183,0.099871,0.10575,0.085092,0.055602]},{"section":12,"text":"However, the disorientation and hallucinations fit.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035635,0.072486,0.083266,0.087804,0.090426,0.091596,0.094035,0.094191,0.092992,0.093175,0.086458,0.077937],"unified_progress":[0.04183,0.067281,0.076385,0.084533,0.089756,0.092903,0.098186,0.097362,0.096445,0.098209,0.087451,0.069658]},{"section":13,"text":"Another possibility is alcoholic hallucinosis.","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034099,0.069808,0.082668,0.090064,0.094989,0.095135,0.096559,0.095749,0.091776,0.092584,0.082069,0.074499],"unified_progress":[0.038299,0.065806,0.08101,0.09138,0.094181,0.097767,0.099343,0.097751,0.094142,0.092307,0.080764,0.067252]},{"section":14,"text":"That usually occurs after longer periods of abstinence, like days to weeks.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035568,0.071472,0.080549,0.088676,0.09613,0.10166,0.10123,0.098886,0.092189,0.090499,0.078368,0.064763],"unified_progress":[0.064531,0.079083,0.084233,0.087527,0.092159,0.097169,0.095149,0.096715,0.0902,0.085919,0.071804,0.055511]},{"section":15,"text":"It's characterized by auditory hallucinations more commonly, but maybe visual ones too.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02907,0.064285,0.077129,0.087314,0.095348,0.099864,0.10424,0.10225,0.0964,0.094934,0.082934,0.066237],"unified_progress":[0.038396,0.064453,0.082206,0.089202,0.096136,0.10117,0.101,0.10154,0.097264,0.097266,0.077009,0.054359]},{"section":16,"text":"But the key here is that it's typically without the confusion or disorientation seen in delirium.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030503,0.063335,0.074819,0.083135,0.089375,0.093511,0.098972,0.099927,0.098032,0.09739,0.090278,0.080722],"unified_progress":[0.037208,0.059122,0.072376,0.081435,0.089377,0.094385,0.097142,0.10094,0.099688,0.10322,0.090609,0.0745]},{"section":17,"text":"Then there's withdrawal seizures, but those usually happen within the first 48 hours, so three days might be a bit late for that.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031991,0.065332,0.075558,0.083459,0.090226,0.095878,0.10018,0.10154,0.098843,0.097244,0.088338,0.071408],"unified_progress":[0.042318,0.066226,0.076354,0.083163,0.090702,0.094788,0.09771,0.10143,0.099368,0.10181,0.08505,0.061079]},{"section":18,"text":"Plus, the patient isn't having seizures now.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028306,0.061787,0.072268,0.079378,0.08593,0.092645,0.10122,0.10557,0.10468,0.10193,0.095741,0.070545],"unified_progress":[0.033604,0.061349,0.072579,0.080046,0.090773,0.093339,0.099129,0.10569,0.1052,0.11163,0.089707,0.056962]},{"section":19,"text":"Wernicke-Korsakoff syndrome involves confusion, ophthalmoplegia, and ataxia, but the case doesn't mention those other signs.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028523,0.062623,0.07522,0.08645,0.094838,0.099656,0.10423,0.10243,0.097883,0.095298,0.084272,0.068579],"unified_progress":[0.032568,0.059936,0.078058,0.088333,0.096102,0.10558,0.10359,0.10491,0.10125,0.097075,0.079041,0.053558]},{"section":20,"text":"The symptoms here are more acute confusion and hallucinations, so maybe not that.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023997,0.056544,0.071151,0.080672,0.087862,0.093579,0.10148,0.10423,0.10451,0.1018,0.096775,0.077402],"unified_progress":[0.032273,0.056768,0.070428,0.07946,0.090054,0.093994,0.098376,0.10464,0.10466,0.11188,0.091651,0.065815]},{"section":21,"text":"The symptoms of disorientation to time, place, person, along with illusions and hallucinations, plus the timing (3 days after stopping alcohol) point more towards delirium tremens.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035894,0.068052,0.073004,0.078048,0.084523,0.090533,0.09437,0.096209,0.097142,0.096609,0.095279,0.090336],"unified_progress":[0.04548,0.063228,0.07076,0.077721,0.084785,0.092552,0.094588,0.097652,0.098705,0.098077,0.094183,0.08227]},{"section":22,"text":"Alcoholic hallucinosis typically doesn't have the severe confusion and disorientation.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030142,0.060837,0.07021,0.07897,0.087458,0.093136,0.098375,0.098993,0.097575,0.097775,0.093871,0.092659],"unified_progress":[0.035875,0.05545,0.069154,0.076482,0.084329,0.093265,0.095207,0.099689,0.10002,0.10126,0.098001,0.091268]},{"section":23,"text":"So DTs seems more likely here.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025036,0.052945,0.066586,0.074115,0.079318,0.082471,0.088046,0.091059,0.095977,0.099786,0.10428,0.14038],"unified_progress":[0.024515,0.040444,0.050097,0.06065,0.065746,0.07577,0.079788,0.090209,0.097903,0.10767,0.13447,0.17274]},{"section":24,"text":"Let me confirm the typical presentation again.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.28415,0.046378,0.047404,0.056989,0.059366,0.063672,0.06244,0.07352,0.078976,0.078154,0.085569,0.063381],"unified_progress":[0.1803,0.068488,0.05876,0.060327,0.069402,0.073111,0.10089,0.087357,0.089078,0.076555,0.072427,0.063299]},{"section":25,"text":"DTs can present with clouding of sensorium, fluctuating consciousness, hallucinations (often vivid and threatening), autonomic hyperactivity.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.053133,0.10665,0.057709,0.092264,0.095844,0.097968,0.096285,0.090662,0.085301,0.081568,0.075207,0.067414],"unified_progress":[0.060649,0.081017,0.061095,0.08639,0.091904,0.095948,0.098047,0.095926,0.093539,0.090281,0.079978,0.065225]},{"section":26,"text":"The case mentions visual illusions and hallucinations, which fit.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03148,0.064435,0.075017,0.082573,0.089645,0.093988,0.097981,0.097499,0.097967,0.094568,0.092856,0.08199],"unified_progress":[0.053079,0.061699,0.070743,0.078027,0.086788,0.093943,0.094525,0.097496,0.097848,0.098118,0.091621,0.076114]},{"section":27,"text":"The disorientation is a key part of delirium, which is central to DTs.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029851,0.06038,0.072244,0.081182,0.088112,0.091783,0.096541,0.096516,0.096494,0.096958,0.093936,0.096004],"unified_progress":[0.043356,0.054575,0.066394,0.075102,0.082117,0.08981,0.092292,0.096578,0.09859,0.1006,0.10129,0.099296]},{"section":28,"text":"So yeah, the most likely diagnosis is delirium tremens.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.022168,0.043677,0.053075,0.060901,0.069244,0.076622,0.084458,0.090026,0.098881,0.10299,0.11743,0.18052],"unified_progress":[0.021888,0.03151,0.039942,0.049167,0.054731,0.068663,0.072337,0.087099,0.10038,0.11048,0.15264,0.21116]}]}}